{{Infobox feature on celestial object |name = Haulani |image = PIA20359 Haulani crater at LAMO crop.jpg |caption = Haulani imaged by ''Dawn'' from [[Dawn (spacecraft)#Mapping orbits|LAMO]] |type = |location = [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] |coordinates= {{coord|5.34|N|10.58|E|globe:ceres_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} |coordinates_footnotes = <ref name="USGS-20150706">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=Planetary Names: Crater, craters: Haulani on Ceres |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/Feature/15338 |date=6 July 2015 |work=[[USGS]] |accessdate=16 July 2015 }}</ref><ref name="USGS-20150713-pdf">{{cite web |author=Staff |title=USGS: Ceres nomenclature |url=http://planetarynames.wr.usgs.gov/images/ceres.pdf |date=13 July 2015 |work=[[USGS]] |format=[[PDF]] |accessdate=16 July 2015 }}</ref> |length = |width = |diameter = {{convert|34|km|mi}} |depth = |area = |dimensions = |peak = |discoverer = |naming = After [[Haulani (mythology)|Haulani]], Hawaiian goddess of plants |eponym = }}
'''Haulani''' {{IPAc-en|h|aʊ|ˈ|l|ɑː|n|i}} is an [[impact crater]] located on [[Ceres (dwarf planet)|Ceres]] that contains "Spot 1", one of the [[bright spots on Ceres|bright spots]] observed by the [[Dawn (spacecraft)|Dawn spacecraft]]. The crater was named after [[Haulani (mythology)|Haulani]], the Hawaiian goddess of plants.<ref name="USGS-20150706" /><ref name="USGS-20150713-pdf" /> In July 2018, NASA released a comparison of physical features, including Haulani crater, found on Ceres with similar ones present on Earth.<ref name="NASA-20180724">{{cite web |last1=Landau |first1=Elizabeth |last2=McCartney |first2=Gretchen |title=What Looks Like Ceres on Earth? |url=https://www.jpl.nasa.gov/news/news.php?feature=7196 |date=24 July 2018 |work=[[NASA]] |accessdate=25 July 2018 }}</ref> <gallery mode=packed caption="Haulani crater" heights=165> File:Haulani crater.jpg File:PIA20146-Ceres-DwarfPlanet-Dawn-3rdMapOrbit-HAMO-image83-20151006.jpg File:PIA20129-Ceres-DwarfPlanet-Dawn-3rdMapOrbit-HAMO-image66-20151014.jpg </gallery><gallery mode=packed heights=165> File:PIA20352-Ceres-DwarfPlanet-Dawn-HaulaniCrater-20150905.jpg|Haulani - in visible/brightness (left); false color/mineralogy; infrared/temperature (5 September 2015). File:PIA20358-Ceres-DwarfPlanet-HaulaniCrater-CloseupColor-20160419.jpg|Haulani in enhanced color </gallery>
