'''Inverse resolution''' is an [[inductive reasoning]] technique that involves [[:wikt:invert|inverting]] the [[resolution (logic)|resolution operator]].
==References== [http://www.doc.ic.ac.uk/~shm/ilp_theory.html#inverse_resolution Inverse resolution] {{logic-stub}}
[[Category:Inductive reasoning]]

'''John Robert Anderson''' (5 March 1928 – 26 February 2007) was an Australian chemist whose research specialised on [[materials science]]. Anderson served as Chief of the Division of Material Sciences at the [[Commonwealth Scientific and Industrial Research Organisation]] from 1970 to 1978. He attended [[Sydney Boys High School]] from 1940 to 1944.<ref>http://www.shsobu.org.au/wp-content/uploads/professors.pdf</ref>

