{|{{Infobox ship begin |infobox caption=RV ''Maurice Ewing''}} <!-- commercial vessels --><!-- caption: yes, nodab, or <caption text> --> {{Infobox ship image |Ship image= |Ship caption= }} {{Infobox ship career |Hide header= |Ship name=*''Bernier'' (1983–1988) *''Maurice Ewing'' (1988–) |Ship namesake=[[Maurice Ewing|William Maurice "Doc" Ewing]] |Ship owner=*Petro Canada (1983–1988) *[[Columbia University]] (1988–) |Ship operator=[[Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory]] |Ship registry= |Ship route= |Ship ordered= |Ship builder= |Ship original cost= |Ship yard number= |Ship way number= |Ship laid down= |Ship launched= |Ship completed= |Ship christened= |Ship acquired= |Ship maiden voyage= |Ship in service= |Ship out of service= |Ship identification=*{{IMO Number|8203153}} *{{MMSI Number|525024131}} *[[Maritime call sign|Callsign]]: JZJF |Ship fate=Retired 2005 |Ship status= |Ship notes= }} {{Infobox ship characteristics |Hide header= |Header caption= |Ship class= |Ship type=[[Research vessel]] |Ship tonnage={{GT|1976}} |Ship displacement= |Ship length={{convert|230|ft|abbr=on}} |Ship beam= |Ship height= |Ship draught= |Ship draft= |Ship depth= |Ship decks= |Ship deck clearance= |Ship ramps= |Ship ice class= |Ship sail plan= |Ship power= |Ship propulsion= |Ship speed={{convert|11|kn}} |Ship endurance=60 days |Ship capacity= |Ship crew= |Ship notes= }} |}'''RV ''Maurice Ewing''''' was a [[research vessel]] operated by the [[Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory]] of [[Columbia University]]. It was retired in 2005 and replaced by [[RV Marcus Langseth|RV ''Marcus Langseth'']] in 2008. Although a multipurpose vessel, ''Maurice Ewing''{{'}}s notable capability was to collect [[reflection seismology|multichannel seismic]] data.
''Maurice Ewing'' was named for [[Maurice Ewing|William Maurice "Doc" Ewing]], [[geophysicist]] and first director of Lamont Geological Observatory (now known as Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory).
The vessel was later renamed several times: - Scan Resolution, Bergan Resolution, the Reflect Resolution, and the NORDIC BAHARI. Still to this day the vessel operates as a multi-streamer seismic research vessel.
== External links == * {{cite web |url=http://www.ldeo.columbia.edu/res/fac/oma/history/ewing.html |title=Maurice Ewing (1988–2005) |department=Marine Operations |website=[[Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory]] |publisher=[[Columbia University]] |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100625215634/http://www.ldeo.columbia.edu/res/fac/oma/history/ewing.html |archivedate=2010-06-25}} * {{cite web |url=http://www.ldeo.columbia.edu |title=Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory |website=[[Lamont-Doherty Earth Observatory]] |publisher=[[Columbia University]]}}
